The Keiser Report  No. 178	
= Max Keiser and Stacy Herbert =
Thursday, 01 September 2011


[sebaygo1]


This time Max and Stacy discuss intergenerational debt for IMF poster children; radical plans for EU banks; and an artist's incendiary painting as bank statement. 

In the second half of the show Max talks to Isa Blumi about the role of micro-finance and oil traders in unrest in Yemen.
